<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1231">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/327.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Canova</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 4. Consul, Tampico, reports that local authorities have not yet
                            received orders to accept New York exchange at prevailing rate. Confer
                            with Hanna and request that such order be repeated at once and that it
                            also be sent Tuxpam authorities since Consul states that production
                            taxes in Panuco Topila fields must be paid in Tuxpam July 15.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>